Subject: regulator: fwnode_regulator: fix IS_ERR() called on int return value

drivers/regulator/fwnode_regulator.c (introduced by the CIX patch
0033-regulator-add-acpi-support.patch) calls IS_ERR() on the int
return value of fwnode_count_reference_with_args(). On Debian 13
(trixie) GCC promotes -Wint-conversion to an error and the build
fails. The intent (made obvious by the immediately following
max(n_phandles, 0)) is to clamp negative error returns to zero, so
replace IS_ERR() with a `< 0` test.

This is a local follow-up to 0033 pending an upstream fix in
cixtech/cix-linux-main.

--- a/drivers/regulator/fwnode_regulator.c
+++ b/drivers/regulator/fwnode_regulator.c
@@ -93,7 +93,7 @@ int fwnode_get_regulation_constraints(struct fwnode_handle *np,
 
 	n_phandles = fwnode_count_reference_with_args(np, "regulator-coupled-with",
 						NULL);
-	if (IS_ERR(n_phandles))
+	if (n_phandles < 0)
 		n_phandles = 0;
 
 	n_phandles = max(n_phandles, 0);
